    <!-- ===================== SECTION FIVE: Equations and Graphs ===================== -->
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDef_6">Solve f(x)=0 → find x-intercepts. g(x)=h(x) → intersection points. Circle: x²+y²=r². Systems: intersections of graphs; lines → one, none, or ∞ solutions.</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefQuestion_6">How many x-intercepts does f(x) = x² − 4 have?</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefAnswerOne_6">0</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefAnswerTwo_6">1</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefAnswerThree_6">2</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_6">2</string>

    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryProperties_6">The x-intercepts of f(x) are the roots of f(x) = 0. Two graphs intersect where their y-values are equal. A circle x²+y²=r² has center (0,0) and radius r. Systems of equations correspond to intersections of their graphs.</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsQuestion_6">Does the circle x² + y² = 25 have radius 5?</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsAnswerOne_6">True</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_6">False</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsAnswerThree_6">Neither</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_6">True</string>

    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExamples_6">Example 1: Solve f(x) = x² − 9 = 0. Roots: x = ±3. These are x-intercepts of the parabola. ✓
Example 2: Find intersections of y = x and y = x². Set equal: x = x² → x²−x=0 → x(x−1)=0 → x=0 or x=1. Points: (0,0) and (1,1). ✓
Example 3: Circle x²+y²=16 has radius 4. Point (4,0) is on the circle: 16+0=16. ✓</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExQuestion_6">What is the radius of the circle x² + y² = 49?</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExAnswerOne_6">5</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExAnswerTwo_6">7</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExAnswerThree_6">9</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExCorrectAnswer_6">7</string>

