    <!-- ===================== SECTION SIX: Inequalities and Graphs ===================== -->
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryDef_6">Solve f(x)&gt;0 → x where graph above axis. Systems: intersection of solution sets. In 2 vars → half-planes; system → overlap region.</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryDefQuestion_6">Is x = 3 in the solution set of f(x) = x − 2 &gt; 0?</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryDefAnswerOne_6">True</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryDefAnswerTwo_6">False</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryDefAnswerThree_6">Neither</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_6">True</string>

    <string name="SectionSixTheoryProperties_6">To solve f(x) &gt; 0 graphically, find the intervals where the graph lies above the x-axis. For inequalities in two variables (e.g. y &gt; kx + b), the solution is a half-plane. The boundary line is included for ≥ or ≤, and excluded for &gt; or &lt;.</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryPropsQuestion_6">For the inequality y &gt; 2x + 1, is the boundary line y = 2x + 1 included in the solution?</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryPropsAnswerOne_6">True</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_6">False</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryPropsAnswerThree_6">Neither</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_6">False</string>

    <string name="SectionSixTheoryWorkedExamples_6">Example 1: Solve x² − 4 &gt; 0 graphically. Roots at x = ±2. Parabola is above x-axis for x &lt; −2 or x &gt; 2. Solution: (−∞,−2) ∪ (2,+∞). ✓
Example 2: Solve x − 3 &gt; 0. Graph y = x − 3 is above x-axis when x &gt; 3. Solution: (3, +∞). ✓
Example 3: Solve system x &gt; 1 and y &lt; 3. Solution is the overlap region: all points (x,y) with x &gt; 1 and y &lt; 3. ✓</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryWorkedExQuestion_6">For f(x) = x − 5, for which x-value does f(x) = 0 (boundary of f(x) &gt; 0)?</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryWorkedExAnswerOne_6">3</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryWorkedExAnswerTwo_6">5</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryWorkedExAnswerThree_6">7</string>
    <string name="SectionSixTheoryWorkedExCorrectAnswer_6">5</string>

